(Real Learning Application) Tj
T*
(In real study situations, students master Programming by practising with tasks that) Tj
T*
(mirror basic algorithm and control-structure questions. The topic becomes more) Tj
T*
(meaningful when it is linked to examples, revision drills, and exam-style questions that) Tj
T*
(reflect how Computer Science is assessed.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Worked Examples) Tj
T*
(Worked Example 1) Tj
T*
(1. Start with an example based on writing a simple program that makes decisions.) Tj
T*
(2. Identify the exact idea in algorithms, logic, sequence, selection, and repetition) Tj
T*
(that the question is testing.) Tj
T*
(3. Apply the correct method for Programming step by step without skipping reasoning.) Tj
T*
(4. Check the final answer and explain why it is correct.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Worked Example 2) Tj
T*
(1. Choose a second example that still focuses on basic algorithm and control-structure) Tj
T*
(questions.) Tj
T*
(2. Break the task into smaller parts and link each part to the rule being used.) Tj
T*
(3. Point out how to avoid coding without first planning the logic while solving it.) Tj
T*
(4. Review the result and connect it back to the topic overview.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Common Mistakes) Tj
T*
(- Misunderstanding the core focus of Programming: algorithms, logic, sequence,) Tj
T*
(selection, and repetition.) Tj
T*
(- Coding without first planning the logic.) Tj
T*
(- Jumping to an answer without showing the steps or reasoning clearly.) Tj
T*
(- Practising Programming without checking whether the method matches the question being) Tj
T*
(asked.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Study Tips) Tj
T*
(- Rewrite the overview of Programming in your own words after studying it.) Tj
T*
(- Use short exercises built around basic algorithm and control-structure questions) Tj
T*
(before trying harder tasks.) Tj
T*
(- Keep track of mistakes such as coding without first planning the logic and write the) Tj
T*
(correction beside each one.) Tj
T*
(- Revise Programming regularly so the method behind algorithms, logic, sequence,) Tj
T*
(selection, and repetition becomes familiar.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Practice Exercises) Tj
T*
(- Explain the overview of Programming and describe how it fits into Computer Science.) Tj
T*
(- Work through an example based on writing a simple program that makes decisions and) Tj
T*
(explain each step.) Tj
T*
